verses.rendering:
His ways prosper at all times;
Your judgments are far above, out of his sight.
All his enemies — he sneers at them.

He sits in ambush near the villages;
in hidden places he murders the innocent.
His eyes watch for the helpless.

He lurks in hiding like a lion in its thicket;
he lurks to seize the poor.
He seizes the poor, dragging them into his net.

O LORD, You have heard the desire of the afflicted;
You steady their hearts;
You incline Your ear,
